  "claim_short": "2308.07668 Proposition 55 L_p({0,1}^kappa) constants c_n and c. Exact finite constants for every n>=1: c_n^p=2-(4-2^p)/2^n for 1<p<=2 and c_n^p=2^(p-1) for 2<=p<infinity. Consequently c=2^(1/p) for 1<p<=2 and c=2^(1-1/p) for 2<=p<infinity. The finite 1<p<2 extremal inequality is identified with the largest normalized p-Laplacian Rayleigh quotient of the complete graph; Amghibech's spectrum as quoted in Zhang...",
